-- Stock funds worldwide attract $6.6 bln over week - BofA
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Fri Jan 24, 2014 09:29AM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Jan 24 (Reuters) - Fund investors worldwide poured $6.6 billion into stock funds in the week ended Jan. 22, bringing inflows into the funds this year to $16 billion, data from a Bank of America Merrill Lynch Global Research report showed on Friday.

European stock funds attracted $4.3 billion, marking 30 straight weeks of inflows, according to the report, which also cited data from fund-tracker EPFR Global. Emerging market stock funds, meanwhile, posted outflows of $2.4 billion, marking their biggest outflows in five weeks.  Bond funds worldwide attracted $2 billion, bringing inflows this year to $8 billion. Riskier high-yield bond funds attracted $1 billion of the new money, marking their fifth straight week of inflows.